  "prompt": "What are the best international schools in Bangalore with the IGCSE Board?",
  "response": "Bangalore is home to several reputable international schools offering the IGCSE curriculum. Here\u2019s a list of some of the best international schools in Bangalore that follow the IGCSE board:\n\n1. **Garden City International School**\n   - Offers a robust academic program with a focus on holistic development.\n   - A variety of extracurricular activities.\n\n2. **Inventure Academy**\n   - Known for its innovative teaching methods and strong emphasis on experiential learning.\n   - Offers a range of IGCSE subjects and an extensive extracurricular program.\n\n3. **The International School Bangalore (TISB)**\n   - Highly regarded for its academic excellence and facilities.\n   - Offers a balance of academics, arts, and sports.\n\n4. **Indus International School**\n   - Offers an international curriculum with a focus on critical thinking and global perspectives.\n   - Strong emphasis on personal development and leadership skills.\n\n5. **Canadian International School**\n   - Provides a diverse learning environment with a variety of IB and IGCSE programs.\n   - Offers extensive extracurricular activities and facilities.\n\n6. **Brigade International School**\n   - Provides a well-rounded education with a blend of academics and co-curricular activities.\n   - Focuses on personal development along with academic achievement.\n\n7. **Stonehill International School**\n   - Offers a comprehensive IGCSE curriculum with a focus on global citizenship and inquiry-based learning.\n   - Known for excellent teaching staff and infrastructure.\n\n8. **Ecole Globale International Girls' School**\n   - A girls' school focusing on IGCSE and IB curriculum.\n   - Emphasizes empowerment, leadership, and education in a supportive environment.\n\n9. **SIS (Singapore International School)**\n   - Follows a blend of Singapore and international curricula, including IGCSE.\n   - Focuses on innovative teaching and a holistic educational approach.\n\nWhen selecting a school, it\u2019s essential to consider factors such as location, fee structure, specific programs offered, and the overall philosophy of the school. Visiting the schools for open days or orientations can also help in making an informed decision.",
